Meetings commemorate Kim Il Sung's birthday 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;    Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Meetings to commemorate the 87th birth anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung were held in provinces, cities and counties and at units of the three services of the Korean People's Army (KPA) on Wednesday.
    Present there were leading officials of local party, power organs and working people's organizations, working people of different social standings, commanding officers of units of the three services of the KPA and their soldiers.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    Reporters that said the birth of the President Kim Il Sung was a solemn historic sunrise which threw rays of national liberation and rebirth over the gloomy land of Korea and a great event which brought about a radical turn in the history of shaping destinies of the people.    Referring to the exploits performed by Kim Il Sung, they noted that he built a powerful driving force of the revolution and the best socialist system which the people consider as their life and soul. This is the noblest revolutionary exploit of the President, the father of socialist Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    They further said:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;    The revolutionary cause of Juche is being successfully carried forward by General Secretary Kim Jong Il and the red flag of the revolution associated with the President's life is more vigorously fluttering.     Upholding the party's slogan "Let this year mark a turning-point in building a powerful nation " we should rise up again and successfully realize the plan of the great Marshal to turn our country into a powerful nation of Juche as we built the powerful socialist country of independence, self-sustenance  and self-reliance in defence through the grand Chollima march.

Cuban ambassador hosts reception
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Cuban ambassador to Korea Jose Manuel Inclan Embade on Wednesday hosted a  reception at the embassy on the occasion of Sun's Day. Invited were Honorary vice-President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly Pak Song Chol and other officials concerned.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Cuban ambassador said that the august name of the respected leader Kim Il Sung, the great man of the world, occupies the most brilliant  place in the world revolutionary movement and the history of the anti-imperialist struggle for his great achievements.   Particularly intimate relations  forged between Fidel Castro and Kim Il Sung are the great pride and glory for the Cuban people, he said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   The Cuban people know well the two leaders directed great efforts to strengthening and developing the friendly and cooperative relations between the two peoples.   Cuba and Korea are in the same trench in the struggle against imperialism. The brotherly friendship between the two countries gives us strength and  courage, faith in victory and optimism about the future.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun said that to strengthen and develop the traditional friendly and cooperative relations with Cuba generation after generation is the intention of the great leader Kim Il Sung in his lifetime and the unshakable will of the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il.    He further said:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   The DPRK will make all its efforts to steadily develop the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries on the basis of the cordial relations between Kim Jong Il and Fidel Castro Ruz.   The Korean people will always send invariable support and solidarity to the friendly Cuban people in their struggle to defend the country, revolution and the gains of socialism from the vicious blockade and suffocation moves of the U.S.

Friendly gathering with Mongolian artistes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- A friendly gathering with Mongolian artistes who are participating in the 17th April Spring Friendship Art Festival took place here on April 14 under the co-sponsorship of the Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and the Korea-Mongolia Friendship Association.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present on invitation were Mongolian artistes, a Mongolian delegation to commemorations of Sun's Day, Mongolian guests, Mongolian ambassador to Korea D. Byambaa and embassy officials.  Present there were Choe Jong Hwan, vice-chairman of the Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and vice-chairman of the Korea-Mongolia Friendship Association, other officials concerned, teachers and students of the Korea-Mongolia friendship Pyongyang Songyo Senior Middle School No. 1.   The participants in the gathering conversed with each other, singing songs of the two countries.

Korean officials meet foreign guests
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, member of the political bureau of the C.C., the Worker's Party of Korea and President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly (SPA) of the DPRK, met and had a conversation with Alberto Moreno, general secretary of the c.c., the Communist Party of Peru (Red Motherland), at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the SPA presidium and chairman of the Korean Social Scientists Society, met and conversed with Kenichi Ogami, secretary general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea (IIJI), and his party  as well as  Prof. And Dr. Alexandr Kovalyov  of Moscow State University of Russia  who is director of the board of the IIJI, on the same day.  Jang Chol, chairman of the organizing committee of the 17th April Spring Friendship Art Festival,  met and had a conversation with Russian Alexandrov Army Choir and Dance Ensemble on the same day.

Joint performances of spring festival given
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Joint performances of the 17th April Spring Friendship Art Festival were given at theatres here on April 14.  Appreciating the performances were Kim Yong Nam, Pak Song Chol, Hong Song Nam and other party and state leading officials.Among those in the audience were a delegation of the Koreans in Japan led by So Man Sul, first vice-chairman of the central standing committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan, Choe Hong Hui, president of the International Taekwon-do Federation, and other overseas Koreans, foreign diplomatic envoys here and embassy officials and foreign guests.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Songs, dances, instrumental music  and other  numbers were put on stages.   The performers highly praised the brilliant life of the President Kim Il Sung and the greatness of General Secretary Kim Jong Il.   They also represented well the aspiration and desire of the world's progressive people to  fully enjoy an independent and creative life in happiness in a freeï¿½@and peaceful, new world, their people's ardent love  of their homelands and native places  as well as their diligent and cheerful work and noble spiritual world.   Joint performances continue.

Ceremony held to preserve car sent by Kim Il Sung
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- A ceremony of preserving a car sent by the President Kim Il Sung to the first Cuban ambassador to Korea was held at the Cuban embassy here on April 14.   The embassy officials have  serviced and preserved the car sent by the President  in its original state in order to convey his noble  sense of internationalist  obligation down to posterity on the occasion of Sun's Day, a significant holiday common to humankind.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Present at the ceremony were Pak Song Chol, Honorary vice-president of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, Kim Il Chol, Minister of the People's Armed Forces, Paek Nam Sun, Foreign Minister, and  other officials concerned.   Cuban ambassador to Korea Jose Manuel Inclan Embade said at the ceremony:&nbsp;&nbsp; "I am convinced that the car will be a symbol and  vivid  evidence of our fraternal friendship."

Symposium "the present times and the national culture" held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- The 2nd symposium on "present times and national culture" was held here on Wednesday.   The symposium was attended by chairman of the c.c., the General Federation  of the Unions of Literature and the Arts of Korea Jang Chol, officials concerned, foreign  men and women of culture and art and overseas. Korean artistes who are participating in the 17th April Spring Friendship Art Festival.   At the symposium, Jang Chol delivered a report on ushering in a new era of independent national art by  properly carrying forward and developing  national cultural heritage.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He recalled national cultural heritage has been properly carried forward and developed in  Korea under the wise leadership of the President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il.   Korean national art, which is vibrant with the soul and spirit of Korea and its fragrance, is noble and national in its nature  that strikes the world people with admiration, and belongs to  cultural treasure of mankind, he said.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean men and women of culture and art will strengthen solidarity, cooperation and exchange with the world's progressive men and women of culture and art, guided by the idea of independence, peace and friendship and positively support and encourage them in their efforts to build independent national culture and art, he noted, calling for strenuous efforts to frustrate the imperialists' moves for war of aggression and their ideological and cultural poisoning and build a new world, peaceful and independent.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Taking the floor at the symposium were Korean musical critic Kim Tuk Chong, chairman Kim Jong Su of the central standing committee of the Union of Korean Literary Men and Artists in Japan,  poet V.S. Kraulin, vice-chairman of the "Peace and Today" Committee of Russia, Prof. And Dr. Shafwat Kamal of the Research Center of the Folk Academy in Cairo and g. Namsuren, director for research of  Mongolian University of Culture and Art.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The speakers introduced successes and experience gained in carrying forward national cultural heritage and building national art and touched on the issues of revitalizing the national art movement.   They  were of the view that for each country and nation to carry forward and develop their national cultural heritage on the principle of independence and historicism is the way of making a substantial contribution to adding shine to national art and enriching the art treasure of mankind.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They underscored the need to further strengthen the solidarity and cooperation among the progressive men and women of culture and art in order to  preserve and develop national art.

Papers commemorate Sun's Day
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Papers here today dedicate special write-ups to Sun's Day, the birth anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung.   Front-paging Portraits of the President, the press devotes all its pages to editorials underscoring the necessity to build a powerful nation, true to his behest, and to  accounts of commemoration events.   Seen there are an account of a national meeting held here to commemorate the 87th birth anniversary of the President, a report made by premier Hong Song Nam at the meeting and accounts of meetings held in all provinces, cities and counties and at units of the three services of the Korean People's Army.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is reported in the press that General Secretary Kim Jong Il sent books and equipment to the Grand People's Study House  and Educational Aid Fund and Stipend for the children of Koreans in Japan on the occasion of Sun's Day.   Highlighted in the press is news that Kim Jong Il received floral baskets, gifts and congratulatory letters from the general secretary of the c.c., the Communist Party of Peru (Red Motherland), the general secretary of the c.c., the Communist Party of Bangladesh (Marxist-Leninist), the delegation of the Finland-Korea Association, officials of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, foreign diplomatic envoys and embassies here.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Papers carry letters to Kim Jong Il from the central committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea and the central standing committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan.   Papers report that a ceremony of preserving a car sent by Kim Il Sung to the first Cuban ambassador to Korea was held at the Cuban embassy here, foreigners visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace to pay homage to him and officials of foreign embassies  in charge of cultural affair and friendly relations and members of the mission of the world food program here laid floral baskets before his statue on Mansu Hill.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Given in the press are accounts of a joint national meeting of the Korean Children's Union, a central meeting of Koreans in Japan and performances of art circle members of schoolchildren.   The press gives accounts of joint performances of the 17th April Spring Friendship Art Festival and the 2nd symposium on "present times and national culture."

Editorials call for building powerful nation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Papers here today editorially call for building a powerful nation, true to the behest of the President Kim Il Sung.   Editorials commemorate his birth anniversary, Sun's Day.   Rodong Sinmun says:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   We are building a powerful nation of Juche, guided by the ideology and line of Kim Il Sung.   To build a powerful nation as the president wished in his lifetime is the general objective of the respected Kim Jong Il and the starting point of all his thinking and activity.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Over the last 5 years, Kim Jong Il has devotedly worked for the prosperity of the nation with noble patriotism and loyalty.   Whenever a miraculous success is made in the revolution and construction, he attributes it to the President's exploits. This is a noble trait of Kim Jong Il, who leads the building of a powerful nation.   Our nation is becoming thriving and powerful under Kim Jong Il's politics.   Our powerful socialist state is named after Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. It is the Korean people's great honor and pride to live and make revolution in this land that always shines with the name of the sun.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   All people should unite firm around the party headed by Kim Jong Il, exalt our glorious motherland as Kim Il Sung's Korea and complete the building of a powerful socialist nation.   Minju Joson calls for completing the President's cause generation after generation under the leadership of Kim Jong Il and exalt Korea as the nation of the great sun.

Central meeting of Koreans in Japan held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, April 14 (KNS-KCNA) -- A central meeting of Koreans in Japan was held in Tokyo on  Wednesday on the occasion of the 87th birth anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung.   Present at the meeting were chairman Han Tok Su  and chief vice-chairman Ho Jong Man of the central standing committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), and other  officials of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Han Tok Su stressed in his address at the meeting that Koreans in Japan should uphold the President Kim Il Sung as the eternal sun of Juche and work hard for the prosperity and development of their homeland under the leadership of General Secretary Kim Jong Il.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ho jong man said in his report that the President Kim Il Sung was the great leader  whom the Korean people  acclaimed for the first time in the  nation's history  spanning 5,000 years.   The efforts exerted by him for the Koreans in Japan all his life, his precious teachings and deep care  for them will always remain shining in the history of the movement of Koreans in Japan, Ho noted. He appealed to the Koreans in Japan to single-hearted unite around Marshal Kim Jong Il and vigorously advance for  the progress of the patriotic movement of Koreans in Japan with the  firm conviction of victory.

Party and state leading officials pay homage to Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Party and state leading officials visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace today, Sun's Day, to pay homage to the President Kim Il Sung.  Among the visitors were Kim Yong Nam, Ri Jong Ok Pak Song Chol, Hong Song Nam and other party and state leading officials, members and alternate members of the C.C., the Worker's Party of Korea in Pyongyang, senior officials of the party and armed forces organs, power bodies, public organisations, ministries and national institutions.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A floral basket was laid before the statue of the President in the joint name of the Central Committee of the WPK, the Party Central Military Commission, the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and the cabinet of the DPRK.   The party and state leading officials paid respectful tribute to the statue of the President.   They entered a hall where he is preserved in state and made a bow in humble reverence.   They saw round orders and medals awarded to the President in different countries, a train used by him during his on-site guidance and foreign tour and a car used by him during the last period of his life.

Floral baskets laid before Kim Il Sung's statues
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Working people, servicemen, youth and students across the country laid floral baskets, bunches of flowers and bouquets before the statues of the President Kim Il Sung today, Sun's Day.  Working people, servicemen, youth and students in Pyongyang visited the statue of the President on Mansu Hill.   Standing before the statue was a floral basket sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Amid the playing of the floral basket-laying music, floral baskets, bunches of flowers and bouquets were laid before the statue in the name of institutions, units of the People's Army, enterprises, organizations, factories, farms, schools and families.   Floral baskets, bunches of flowers and bouquets were also laid before the statues of the president at Kim Il Sung University, Kim Il Sung University of politics, the Ministry of Public Security, the Korean Film Studio, the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace and other parts in Pyongyang.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, working people, servicemen, youth and students across the country laid floral baskets, bunches of flowers and bouquets before his statues in their residential quarters.
